Unlike safety-specific transformational leadership, safety-specific active transactional leadership improves employees’ safety performance by clearly conveying contingent incentives and penalties and providing active supervision. Previous research has indicated that safety-specific active transactional leadership can motivate subordinates to obey safety regulations and seek to avoid mistakes and punishment (
  Wallace and Chen, 2006; 
  Wallace et al., 2008; 
  Kark et al., 2015). When motivated by a leader who provides clear incentives and penalties, employees pay more attention to possible rewards and losses, and thus remain highly sensitive to near misses in safety management. Therefore, we propose the following hypothesis:
